name: Shuckle
flavorText: It stores Berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards. Then, put a card from your hand on the bottom of your deck.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Burmy
flavorText: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.

name: Wormadam
flavorText: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokemon's body. The cloak is never shed.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from each of your Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Mothim
flavorText: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the Combee hive.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your Wormadam to another of your Pokemon.

name: Snivy
flavorText: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.
Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Servine
flavorText: When it gets dirty, its leaves can't be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon, you may flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Serperior
flavorText: It can stop its opponents' movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's attacks do 60 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: This Pokemon can't use Slashing Strike during your next turn.

name: Deerling
flavorText: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokemon's fur. People use it to mark the seasons.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Pokemon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Moltres
flavorText: One of the legendary bird Pokemon. It is said that its appearance indicates the coming of spring.
Attack2Text: You may do 40 more damage. If you do, this Pokemon does 20 damage to itself.

name: Fennekin
flavorText: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Fennekin
flavorText: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon with his or her Active Pokemon.

name: Braixen
flavorText: When the twig is plucked from its tail, friction sets the twig alight. The flame is used to send signals to its allies.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Delphox
flavorText: Using psychic power, it generates a fiery vortex of 5,400 degree Fahrenheit, incinerating foes swept into this whirl of flame.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage times the amount of Energy attached to all Pokemon in play.

name: Delphox BREAK
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for a Fire Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokemon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Seel
flavorText: Covered with light blue fur, its hide is thick and tough. It is active in bitter cold of -40 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Dewgong
flavorText: Its streamlined body has little drag in water. The colder the temperature, the friskier it gets.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed. If tails, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Omanyte
flavorText: Revived from an ancient fossil, this Pokemon uses air stored in its shell to sink and rise in water.

name: Omastar
flavorText: Once wrapped around its prey, it never lets go. It eats the prey by tearing at it with sharp fangs.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for a Restored Pokemon and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Omastar BREAK
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon-EX with his or her Active Pokemon.

name: Glaceon-EX
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from Evolution Pokemon.

name: White Kyurem
flavorText: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon has any Fire Energy attached to it, this attack does 20 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: This Pokemon can't attack during your next turn.

name: Binacle
flavorText: They stretch and then contract, yanking their rocks along with them in bold hops. They eat seaweed that washes up on the shoreline.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

name: Barbaracle
flavorText: Barbaracle's legs and hands have minds of their own, and they will move independently. But they usually follow the head's orders.
Ability1Text: If you have a Stadium card in play, your opponent can't attach any Special Energy cards from his or her hand to his or her Pokemon.

name: Rotom
flavorText: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a basic Energy card and attach it to this Pokemon. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Move 2 damage counters from each of your Pokemon to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Alakazam-EX
Ability1Text: When you play M Alakazam-EX from your hand to evolve this Pokemon, before it evolves, you may put 2 damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokemon and 3 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on each of your opponent's Pokemon that has any Energy attached to it.

name: M Alakazam-EX
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Koffing
flavorText: Lighter-than-air gases in its body keep it aloft. The gases not only smell, they are also explosive.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Koffing and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Weezing
flavorText: Very rarely, a sudden mutation can result in two small Koffing twins becoming conjoined as a Weezing.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, discard 2 cards from the top of your opponent's deck.
Attack2Text: Both Active Pokemon are now Confused and Poisoned.

name: Mew
flavorText: Its DNA is said to contain the genetic codes of all Pokemon, so it can use all kinds of techniques.
Ability1Text: This Pokemon can use the attacks of any of your Basic Pokemon in play. (You still need the necessary Energy to use each attack.)
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Pokemon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Spoink
flavorText: It bounces around on its tail to keep its heart pumping. It carries a pearl from Clamperl on its head.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Grumpig
flavorText: It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does an odd dance to gain control over foes.
Attack1Text: Put a Basic Pokemon from your opponent's discard pile onto his or her Bench. Then, put 3 damage counters on that Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Your opponent switches his or her Active Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon.

name: Gothita
flavorText: They intently observe both Trainers and Pokemon. Apparently, they are looking at something only Gothita can see.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Solosis
flavorText: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.
Attack1Text: If Solosis is on your Bench, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Duosion
flavorText: When their two divided brains think the same thoughts, their psychic power is maximized.
Attack1Text: If Solosis is on your Bench, this attack does 30 more damage. If Duosion is on your Bench, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Reuniclus
flavorText: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.
Attack1Text: If Solosis is on your Bench, this attack does 30 more damage. If Duosion is on your Bench, this attack does 60 more damage. If Reuniclus is on your Bench, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Diglett
flavorText: Its skin is very thin. If it is exposed to light, its blood heats up, causing it to grow weak.

name: Marowak
flavorText: The bone it holds is its key weapon. It throws the bone skillfully like a boomerang to KO targets.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks done to you or your hand by your opponent's Pokemon. Remove any existing effects.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 60 damage times the number of heads.

name: Kabuto
flavorText: This Pokemon was regenerated from the fossil of an ancient creature. It protects itself with a hard shell.

name: Kabutops
flavorText: A slim and fast swimmer. It slices its prey with its sharp sickles and drinks the body fluids.
Attack1Text: Heal from this Pokemon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Larvitar
flavorText: Born deep underground, it comes aboveground and becomes a pupa once it has finished eating the surrounding soil.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Larvitar
flavorText: Born deep underground, it comes aboveground and becomes a pupa once it has finished eating the surrounding soil.
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

name: Pupitar
flavorText: Its shell is as hard as sheet rock, and it is also very strong. Its thrashing can topple a mountain.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage. If tails, this Pokemon does 20 damage to itself.

name: Regirock-EX
Ability1Text: The attacks of your Fighting Pokemon (excluding Regirock-EX) do 10 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokemon by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Regirock-EX
Ability1Text: The attacks of your Fighting Pokemon (excluding Regirock-EX) do 10 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokemon by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Wormadam
flavorText: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokemon's body. The cloak is never shed.
Attack2Text: If Mothim is on your Bench, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Riolu
flavorText: The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Riolu
flavorText: The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Lucario
flavorText: By reading the auras of all things, it can tell how others are feeling from over half a mile away.

name: Hawlucha
flavorText: With its wings, it controls its position in the air. It likes to attack from above, a maneuver that is difficult to defend against.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Carbink
flavorText: It has slept underground for hundreds of millions of years since its birth. It's occasionally found during the excavation of caves.
Ability1Text: Basic Energy attached to your Basic Pokemon can't be discarded by effects of your opponent's attacks, Abilities, or Trainer cards.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Carbink
flavorText: It has slept underground for hundreds of millions of years since its birth. It's occasionally found during the excavation of caves.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokemon by your opponent's Pokemon-EX.

name: Carbink BREAK
Attack1Text: Attach 2 Energy cards from your discard pile to 1 of your Fighting Pokemon.

name: Zygarde
flavorText: It's hypothesized that it's monitoring those who destroy the ecosystem from deep in the cave where it lives.
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon with his or her Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon is a Darkness or Fairy Pokemon, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Zygarde
flavorText: It's hypothesized that it's monitoring those who destroy the ecosystem from deep in the cave where it lives.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Zygarde-EX
Attack1Text: If there is any Stadium card in play, this attack does 20 more damage.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Zygarde-EX
Attack1Text: If there is any Stadium card in play, this attack does 20 more damage.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Umbreon-EX
Attack1Text: Discard as many cards as you like from your hand. Then, draw that many cards.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Mega Evolution Pokemon is Knocked Out by damage from this attack, take 2 more Prize cards.

name: Tyranitar
flavorText: If it rampages, it knocks down mountains and buries rivers. Maps must be redrawn afterward.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon, you may attach 1 Darkness Energy from your discard pile to this Pokemon for each Prize card your opponent has taken.
Attack1Text: Discard the top 2 cards of your deck. This attack does 50 more damage for each Supporter card discarded in this way.

name: Vullaby
flavorText: Their wings are too tiny to allow them to fly. They guard their posteriors with bones that were gathered by Mandibuzz.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Mandibuzz
flavorText: Watching from the sky, they swoop to strike weakened Pokemon on the ground. They decorate themselves with bones.
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon that has an Ability. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Wormadam
flavorText: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokemon's body. The cloak is never shed.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage times the number of damage counters on this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

name: Bronzor
flavorText: Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokemon during your opponent's next turn.

name: Bronzong
flavorText: Ancient people believed that petitioning Bronzong for rain was the way to make crops grow.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of your opponent's attacks, including damage, done to your Benched Pokemon.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokemon by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Bronzong BREAK
Attack1Text: Discard as many Metal Energy attached to this Pokemon as you like. For each Energy card discarded in this way, choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon and do 30 damage to it. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance. (You may choose the same Pokemon more than once.)

name: Lucario
flavorText: By reading the auras of all things, it can tell how others are feeling from over half a mile away.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.
Attack2Text: If you have fewer Pokemon in play than your opponent, this attack does 60 more damage for each Pokemon fewer you have in play.

name: Genesect-EX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put a Pokemon Tool card attached to this Pokemon into your hand.
Attack1Text: Discard as many Metal Energy attached to this Pokemon as you like. This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy card discarded in this way.

name: Jigglypuff
flavorText: If it inflates to sing a lullaby, it can perform longer and cause sure drowsiness in its audience.

name: Wigglytuff
flavorText: The body is soft and rubbery. When angered, it will suck in air and inflate itself to an enormous size.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokemon by attacks is reduced by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 60 damage times the number of heads.

name: Mr. Mime
flavorText: It is adept at conning people. It is said to be able to create walls out of thin air by miming.
Attack1Text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw a number of cards equal to the number of cards in your opponent's hand.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

name: Snubbull
flavorText: Small Pokemon flee from its scary face. It is, however, considered by women to be cute.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: M Altaria-EX
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon has any Special Energy attached to it, this attack does 30 more damage and heal 30 damage from each of your Pokemon.

name: Cottonee
flavorText: Perhaps because they feel more at ease in a group, they stick to others they find. They end up looking like a cloud.

name: Whimsicott
flavorText: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.
Attack1Text: Move an Energy from this Pokemon to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Diancie-EX
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is your Active Pokemon, any damage done to your Pokemon by an opponent's attack is reduced by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: If there is any Stadium card in play, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Kingdra-EX
Attack1Text: Discard any Stadium card in play.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each basic Lightning Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Meowth
flavorText: Adores round objects. It wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon that has any damage counters on it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Kangaskhan
flavorText: If it is safe, the young gets out of the belly pouch to play. The adult keeps a close eye on the youngster.

name: Aerodactyl
flavorText: This vicious Pokemon is said to have flown in ancient skies while shrieking high-pitched cries.
Attack2Text: Discard a Special Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Snorlax
flavorText: Its stomach can digest any kind of food, even if it happens to be moldy or rotten.
Attack1Text: This attack can be used even if this Pokemon is Asleep. If it is, this attack does 90 more damage.
Attack2Text: Heal from this Pokemon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Lugia
flavorText: It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is your Active Pokemon, any damage done by attacks from your opponent's Active Pokemon is reduced by 20 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon-EX, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Lugia BREAK
Attack1Text: Discard 2 Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Whismur
flavorText: If it senses danger, it scares the foe by crying out with the volume of a jet-plane engine.
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 damage times the number of your Pokemon that have the Round attack.

name: Loudred
flavorText: The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Exploud
flavorText: Its roar in battle shakes the ground like a tremorâ€“or like an earthquake has struck.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.
Attack2Text: At the end of your opponent's next turn, discard the Defending Pokemon and all cards attached to it.

name: Altaria-EX
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon was healed during this turn, this attack does 60 more damage and heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon has no Weakness.

name: Audino-EX
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each of your Benched Pokemon.

name: M Audino-EX
Attack1Text: If you played a Supporter card from your hand during this turn, this attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Minccino
flavorText: These Pokemon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.
Attack1Text: Discard a Pokemon Tool card attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon.
